## Usage Guidelines

### Import Examples

```typescript
// CDK imports
import { AXAccordionGroupDirective } from '@acorex/cdk/accordion';
import { AXDragDirective } from '@acorex/cdk/drag-drop';
import { AXOverlayService } from '@acorex/cdk/overlay';

// Charts imports
import { AXBarChartComponent } from '@acorex/charts/bar-chart';
import { AXLineChartComponent } from '@acorex/charts/line-chart';

// Components imports
import { AXButtonComponent } from '@acorex/components/button';
import { AXDataTableComponent } from '@acorex/components/data-table';

// Core imports
import { AXTranslationService } from '@acorex/core/translation';
import { AXDateTimeService } from '@acorex/core/date-time';
import { AXValidationService } from '@acorex/core/validation';
```

### Best Practices

1. **Use Specific Imports**: Always import from the most specific entry point (e.g., `@acorex/components/button` instead of `@acorex/components`)
2. **Tree-Shaking**: Granular imports enable better tree-shaking and smaller bundle sizes
3. **Consistent Naming**: All exports follow the `AX` prefix convention
4. **TypeScript Support**: All packages include full TypeScript definitions
5. **Module vs Standalone**: Some packages provide both Module and Standalone component exports

### Common Scenarios & What to Use

When building features, refer to these mappings:

#### UI Components & Forms

- **Buttons**: Use `@acorex/components/button`
- **Form inputs**: Use `@acorex/components/text-box`, `@acorex/components/number-box`, `@acorex/components/password-box`, etc.
- **Date/Time selection**: Use `@acorex/components/datetime-picker`, `@acorex/components/datetime-box`, `@acorex/components/calendar`
- **Dropdowns & Selection**: Use `@acorex/components/select-box`, `@acorex/components/dropdown`, `@acorex/components/autocomplete`
- **File handling**: Use `@acorex/components/uploader` + `@acorex/core/file`
- **Rich text**: Use `@acorex/components/wysiwyg`
- **Code editing**: Use `@acorex/components/code-editor`

